news.title: Blackstone plans India's maiden retail properties REIT, portfolio valued over $2 billion
news.para: Blackstone’s portfolio of income-producing retail assets for this REIT is estimated to be valued in the range of $2.2-2.5 billion, or about Rs 16,500-18,750 crore.

news.title: Dream11 co-founder's wife buys luxury duplex in South Mumbai for Rs 72 crore
news.para: While this is a single amalgamated duplex on the 29th and 30th floors, the apartments in the north and south wing of the tower have been registered separately. These apartments have been amalgamated with permission from the Municipal Corporation of Greater Mumbai.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA lists 3,425 projects as 'lapsed' across state
news.para: Earlier, 3,371 projects were listed in October, of which 210 received extension, and 200 more projects were added to the list, stated the authorities.

news.title: Adani Realty bids for premium home project in BKC, Mumbai
news.para: Radius Estates and Developers, the company that owns Ten BKC, was admitted for insolvency proceedings on April 30 by the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT).

news.title: Blackstone affiliates to buy Bluerock REIT in $3.6 billion deal
news.para: As part of the deal, expected to close in the second quarter of next year, Blackstone will acquire all outstanding shares of the real estate investment trust (REIT) for $24.25 per share - a 57% premium to Bluerock's last closing price of $15.44.

news.title: Special CBI court in Mumbai rejects Avantha Group promoter's bail plea
news.para: The ED is also probing the alleged transaction between Thapar's Avantha Realty, Rana Kapoor and the latter's wife, and has filed a money laundering case after taking cognisance of an FIR lodged by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI).

news.title: ED arrests ex-Unitech promoters Sanjay & Ajay Chandra
news.para: They said the brothers were taken into custody on Monday and have been brought to Delhi from Mumbai where they were lodged in separate jails in an alleged cheating case filed by the Delhi Police.

news.title: Seventeen industrial plots up for grabs in Greater Noida
news.para: The plots are in sectors Ecotech-10, Ecotech 1 Extension 1, Ecotech 1 Extension, Udyog Kendra Ecotech 3 and Udyog Kendra 1 Ecotech 3.

news.title: SBI acquires minority stake worth Rs 100 crore in JSW Cement via CCPS
news.para: Parth Jindal, managing director of JSW Cement said, "In a short span of three years, we have increased our capacity from 6MTPA to 14MTPA and are now working towards achieving the 25MTPA milestone over the next 24 months."

news.title: Gruhas Proptech plans to launch $150 million-proptech focused fund
news.para: Gruhas, focused on real estate investments and prop tech, is promoted by entrepreneur Pai and Zerodha's co-founder Nikhil Kamath.

news.title: Tribals in Madhya Pradesh village say they got thatched huts under PMAY
news.para: Officials conducted a probe and said that only one house in Gaura Kanhari village was found to be "substandard". Locals, however, said that nearly two dozen houses built under the central scheme are of the same type.

news.title: Encroachments in commercial areas across Chandigarh increase fire risk too
news.para: The anti-encroachment drives are hardly making any effect on the ground. Since the fire safety is also directly connected with it, the authorities have their hands really full, especially during the festival seasons.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Panel may review relaxations mooted in area development scheme
news.para: The committee also decided to circulate the Malayalam version of the summary of changes proposed in the area development scheme among the nine councillors of wards coming under the scheme.

news.title: Real estate sector expected to surpass $5 billion funds flow in 2022: JLL
news.para: According to JLL report, 2021 witnessed 31 deals during the first nine months as against 19 deals during the same period of 2020. Unless some large portfolio deals are not inked at the end of the year, annual investments are expected to be in the USD 3.8-4 billion range in 2021, it said.

news.title: KP Park tenements builder paid 90 lakh bonus: Arappor Iyakkam
news.para: Arappor Iyakkam has written to the chief minister and the chief secretary, demanding that an inquiry be conducted and action initiated against senior officials of the TNSCB who approved the payment when the contractor has built a sub-standard facility.
